00:48:35.734 --> 00:48:37.067
Fitzpatrick:
You hire bigger fish.

00:48:37.067 --> 00:48:38.734
Collins-Sussman:
That's it.

00:48:38.734 --> 00:48:40.901
If you're talking about
in a corporate environment,

00:48:40.901 --> 00:48:42.234
if I were in that situation,

00:48:42.234 --> 00:48:44.734
I would start looking around
for bigger fish, right?

00:48:44.734 --> 00:48:46.901
"Where are
the really hard projects?

00:48:46.901 --> 00:48:49.567
"Where are the people who are
much more knowledgeable than me?

00:48:49.567 --> 00:48:52.567
How can I somehow get involved
with what they're doing," right?

00:48:52.567 --> 00:48:55.067
And maybe it's just
slow involvement at first,

00:48:55.067 --> 00:48:58.567
but try to sort of creep
your career in that direction,

00:48:58.567 --> 00:49:00.667
because if you're not
being challenged,

00:49:00.667 --> 00:49:02.734
if you're not a little bit
scared all the time,

00:49:02.734 --> 00:49:04.901
just a little bit,
then you're not gonna improve.

00:49:04.901 --> 00:49:07.067
Now, I mean, I--

00:49:07.067 --> 00:49:09.234
That's not
a guaranteed solution.

00:49:09.234 --> 00:49:11.067
Sometimes you may be trapped,

00:49:11.067 --> 00:49:13.767
in which case, I guess I might
