00:53:14.400 --> 00:53:16.901
having users be able to clone
repositories on the site

00:53:16.901 --> 00:53:19.567
and do polls from them
the same way GitHub does.

00:53:19.567 --> 00:53:22.067
But I was saying
there's a balance, right?

00:53:22.067 --> 00:53:26.234
Yeah, people start out forking,
but on the other hand,

00:53:26.234 --> 00:53:28.901
it's a much lower barrier
to participation

00:53:28.901 --> 00:53:30.534
than with a centralized system.

00:53:30.534 --> 00:53:33.400
So I think
it balances out, right?

00:53:33.400 --> 00:53:35.734
Or maybe it's even better
in the long run

00:53:35.734 --> 00:53:38.400
for participation.

